summary: This is an email from an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York regarding a corrected search warrant binder for a premises search. The correction involves updating the time a cell site simulator located a phone at the subject premises from the previous night to the morning of the warrant execution.

persons.name: Assistant United States Attorney Southern District of New York
persons.context: The sender of the email who is providing a corrected search warrant binder to be sworn out before a judge.

events.title: Correction of Search Warrant Binder
events.description: An Assistant United States Attorney sends a corrected search warrant binder, with the key change being the time a cell site simulator located a phone at the subject premises (from 10:15pm the previous night to 7:36am that morning).
personsInvolved: Assistant United States Attorney Southern District of New York

keyFacts: A corrected search warrant binder was prepared for a premises search in the Southern District of New York.
The correction specifically involved the time a cell site simulator located a target phone at the subject premises, changing it from 10:15pm to 7:36am.
The FBI had reviewed and was comfortable with the corrected warrant, and it was ready to be sworn out before a judge.
